        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                    <p><img src="https://CarnabySnaps.github.io/travel-photography-china/media/posts/26/China-Trip-2014-Beijing-1-36.webp" class="type:primaryImage" alt="" /></p>
                <p>I catch a bullet train from Shanghai to Beijing and on my second day I take the advice of a Chinese passenger from the train who told me “Don’t waste the clear skies!” so I arrange a day trip with a taxi driver to <em>The Great Wall of China</em>, the <em>Mutianyu</em> section which I read is less busy than the popular <em>Badaling</em> part, and was rewarded with clear skies and virtually having the wall to myself! In the next few days I also visited <span class="st"><em>The Forbidden</em> <em>City, </em></span><em>Beijing Olympic Park, The Temple of Heaven, The CCTV headquarters building and Beihai Park.</em></p>
